A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 7 of Chapter 4 of Title 49 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to medical assistance generally, so as to require the Department of Community
3 Health to conduct an annual review of medications and treatment for sickle cell disease for
4 Medicaid recipients; to provide for public input; to provide for an annual report; to provide
5 for related matters; to provide for a short title; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other
6 purposes.
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
8 SECTION 1.
9 This Act shall be known and may be cited as the "Sickle Cell Disease Protection Act."
10 SECTION 2.
11 Article 7 of Chapter 4 of Title 49 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
12 medical assistance generally, is amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
13 "49-4-159.5.
14 (a) The department shall conduct an annual review of all medications, forms of treatment,
15 and services that are eligible for coverage under the Medicaid program for Medicaid
