16 recipients with a diagnosis of sickle cell disease. The purpose of the annual review shall
17 be to determine if the available covered medications, treatments, and services are adequate
18 to meet the needs of Medicaid recipients with a diagnosis of sickle cell disease, and
19 whether the department should seek to add additional medications, treatments, or services.
20 (b) When conducting the annual review required by this Code section, the department shall
21 solicit and consider input from the general public, with specific emphasis on attempting to
22 receive input from persons or groups with knowledge and experience in the area of sickle
23 cell disease treatment.
24 (c) On or before January 15 of each year, the department shall submit a report to the
25 presiding officers of each house of the General Assembly, who shall forward a copy of the
26 report to the chairperson or chairpersons of the appropriate standing committee or
27 committees in each house that details the department's findings from the annual review
28 required by this Code section, as well as any recommendations based upon such findings.
29 The department shall publish the annual report required by this subsection to its public
30 website."
31 SECTION 3.
32 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
